@node Installation "DarkGlow: Installation"

                                  Installation
                                 --------------

- copy the files from drawer plugins2/ to ArtEffect:plugins2/

- copy the Guide whereever you can retrieve it.

After the next start of ArtEffect2+ the menuentry "DarkGlow VR..." should
be available in Menu Filter/Stylize.

@endnode

@node Requirements "DarkGlow: Requirements"

                                  Requirements
                                 --------------

- the only thing you need is ArtEffect2+

@endnode

@node Usage "DarkGlow: Usage"

                                     Usage
                                    -------

   The usage is quite easy, after calling the plugin via menu, you will see a
   little window.

   Just below the preview is a cycle gadget to select wether the plugin should
   work in color or grayscale. Operating in grayscale is faster and will convert
   the picture to gray on-the-fly.

   Radius is the radius around every pixel that will be taken into calculation
   for the actual calculated pixel. E.g. for a Radius of 10 the Matrix has a
   size of 21x21 pixels and is taking 441 surrounding pixels into calculation.

      @{" Colormode " link Colormode}

      @{" Maskmode  " link Maskmode}

      @{" Sliders   " link Sliders}

@endnode

@node Colormode "DarkGlow: Usage of Colormode"

                               Usage of Colormode
                              --------------------

   The decision if an area of the picture should darkglow or not is made based on
   the color of every pixel and the threshold (see @{"Sliders" link Sliders}) as
   long as @{"Maskmode" link Maskmode} is set to normal.

   Default is combined and should be the choice for most effects.

   Combined
   If the sum of all colorchannels (R+G+B) of a pixel is higher than the
   threshold it darkglows. Every pixel darkglows in his own color.

   RGB, R, G, B, RG, RB, GB
   The operation is done on the single colorchannels.
   If the value of a colorchannel is higher than the threshold the pixel darkglows
   in this colorchannel.
   Can be used to underlay e.g. black text on a light background with a darkglow.

   Foreground
   The decision if the pixel should darkglow is done as in "Combined", but the
   actual selected foreground color is used for darkglowing.
   Note: If one drag the slider of ArtEffects color manager fast, there seems
   to be a problem with the messages send to the plugin. It may happen that one
   stops dragging and the plugin will not calculate a new preview.
   One have to force a preview by clicking the preview picture, use a slider in
   the plugin or make a one step color change in the color manager by clicking
   the slider container. This is most probably a overloaded message queue
   anywhere outside the plugin. Nothing I can do about.
   
@endnode

@node Maskmode "DarkGlow: Usage of Maskmode"

                               Usage of Maskmode
                              -------------------

   The mask (stencil in ArtEffect) can be used i a strange way in this plugin.
   It is probably no meant for that, but it was the only way to realize what I
   wanted to.
   The only available mode in grayscale is DarkGlow Out Of, because the grayscale
   picture data does not include the mask.

   Normal
   Operation as usual. Masked areas are blend with the plugin's result.
   For DarkGlow it means also that nothing hidden under the mask can darkglow.

   DarkGlow out of
   Like normal mode, but allows darkglowing to appear from under the masked area.
   Masked areas are still blend with plugin's result as usual.

   DarkGlow Only
   Only areas that are covered by a 100% mask will darkglow. This mode is useful to
   let only some parts of a picture DarkGlow.
   To let the plugin put the result in the picture the mask has to be removed
   from the affected area.
   Unluckily ArtEffect3 does not undo changes in the mask. ArtEffect2 does.
   So, if one uses this feature with ArtEffect3 the effect is not completely
   undoable.
   Let us hope it is a bug in ArtEffect3 and not a feature.

@endnode

@node Sliders "Usage: The Sliders"

                              Usage of the Sliders
                             ----------------------

   Radius
   Higher radius makes the corona bigger, less intense and less objectcontoured.

   Shine
   Changes the appearing of the corona. For values higher than 100% it will
   become less smooth and uneven. That is a feature. If you want a wider corona
   use Radius instead.

   Amount
   Sets the amplification of the effect. It darkens it up.

   Threshold
   Sets the threshold (see @{"Colormode" link Colormode}) that have to be
   exceeded to be a darkglowing pixel.

@endnode

@node Notes "DarkGlow: Notes"

                                     Notes
                                    -------

 - DarkGlow was written on an Amiga 4000 with Cyberstorm MK1 060 and
   compiled with SAS/C 6.58.

 - This PlugIn has no AREXX-Interface and is not localized nor the documentation
   is avaiable in any other language than english (or whatever this is here).
   That may or may not change in the future.

 - If you are interested in getting the information how long an operation took
   try this: setenv VRPLUGINTIMING 1
   

@endnode

